text: Central Buton Regency () is a new regency of Southeast Sulawesi established by separation from Buton Regency under Act No.15 of 2014, dated 23 July 2014. It covers an area of 848.6 km2. The administrative centre lies at Labungkari. It had a population of 86,112 at the 2010 Census. ==Administrative districts== The Central Buton Regency is divided into seven districts (kecamatan),, tabulated below with their areas and 2010 and 2015 Census populations,Biro Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2011.Badan Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2017. the number of administrative villages and the post codes. {| class="sortable wikitable" |- ! The new Regency thus comprises six districts in the southern part of Muna Island together with one district (Talaga Raya) in the southern part of Kabaena Island. It notably does not contain any portion of Buton Island. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Regencies of Southeast Sulawesi
